  "file_summary": "This Java class, `OwnerController`, acts as a Spring MVC controller responsible for handling web requests related to owner management within the PetClinic application. It facilitates the creation, retrieval, updating, and display of owner information. The controller interacts with an `OwnerRepository` to perform data persistence operations. Key functionalities include displaying forms for creating and updating owners, processing form submissions with validation, searching for owners by last name (with pagination support), and displaying individual owner details. It leverages various Spring annotations like `@Controller`, `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`, `@InitBinder`, `@ModelAttribute`, `@RequestParam`, and `@PathVariable` to manage the request flow and data binding, ensuring a robust and user-friendly experience for managing pet owners.",
